content.text:
The Fabric Zoning Lookup (FZL) command is used to lookup a key associated with a Zoning data structure
in the CDC. The FZL command uses the Data Pointer field, as shown in Figure 536.
Upon completion of the Fabric Zoning Lookup (FZL) command, the controller posts a completion queue
entry to the Admin Completion Queue indicating the status of the command. Command specific status
values for the FZL command are defined in Figure 537.
The key associated with the Zoning data structure that matches the specified FZL data (refer to section
8.3.2.3.8) is returned in the completion queue entry Dword 0, as shown in Figure 538.

tables.table_md:
| Definition |  |
| :--- | :--- |
| Zoning Data Structure Locked: | The requested Zoning data structure is locked on the CDC. |
| Zoning Data Structure Not Found: | The requested Zoning data structure does not exist on the CDC. |
| Requested Function Disabled: | Fabric Zoning is not enabled on the CDC. |
| ZoneGroup Originator Invalid: | The DDC is not allowed to access the specified ZoneGroup |
